hopobject.body: Whereabouts in are you from? oxycontin 80 mg online pharmacy Moderate refinancing risk: PREIT has substantial debt maturities of SGD150.42m and SGD187.27m falling due in FY14 and FY15, respectively. On 3 July 2013, PLife REIT successfully secured a five-year committed and unsecured JPY bank loan of JPY7.43bn (SGD97.78m) to refinance 65% of the debt due in FY14. Additionally, PREIT has no outstanding debt under its SGD500m multi-currency MTN programme set up in 2008 and is further supported by un-utilised SGD150m standby loan facilities. The MTN programme and the standby loan facilities are more than adequate to meet debt repayment till end-2017.
